29 7. Subject to subsection 10 of NRS 451.571 and 451.597, the
30 rights of the person to which a part passes under NRS 451.571 are
31 superior to the rights of all others with respect to the part. The
32 person may accept or reject an anatomical gift in whole or in part.
33 Subject to the terms of the document of gift and NRS 451.500 to
34 451.598, inclusive, a person that accepts an anatomical gift of an
35 entire body may allow embalming, burial or cremation, and use of
36 remains in a funeral service. If the gift is of a part, the person to
37 which the part passes under NRS 451.571, upon the death of the
38 donor and before embalming, burial or cremation, shall cause the
39 part to be removed without unnecessary mutilation.
40 8. Neither the physician who attends the decedent at death nor
41 the physician who determines the time of the decedent’s death may
42 participate in the procedures for removing or transplanting a part
43 from the decedent.
