12 11. A procurement organization may transport, or arrange
13 for the transportation of, the body or part of a deceased donor as
14 necessary to facilitate an anatomical gift, including, without
15 limitation, to facilitate:
16 (a) The removal or transplant of a part that is the subject of an
17 anatomical gift; or
18 (b) The return of the remainder of a body from which a part
19 that was the subject of an anatomical gift was removed to the
20 custody of the person under obligation to dispose of the body.
21 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
